<subSubSection lastPageId="130" lastPageNumber="131" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="129.[151,1436,1952,2014]" lastBlockId="130.[151,1436,151,320]" lastPageId="130" lastPageNumber="131" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,236,1953,1977]" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Range:</emphasis>
The species mostly occurs in the cold temperate waters of the North Pacific and ranges into Korean waters during March to October, with peaks of occurrence between May and August. Along the east coast of 
<collectingCountry box="[1328,1399,1990,2013]" name="South Korea" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Korea</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stejneger" authorityYear="1883" class="Mammalia" family="Hyperoodontidae" genus="Berardius" kingdom="Animalia" lastPageId="130" lastPageNumber="131" order="Cetacea" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bairdii">
<emphasis italics="true" lastPageId="130" lastPageNumber="131" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">B. bairdii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
migrates from the North as far South as Jumunjin Pier (central east coast) and returns to the North in October (
<figureCitation box="[256,341,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 86" captionStartId="130.[151,250,1865,1887]" captionTargetBox="[340,1247,375,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@130.[340,1247,375,1843]" captionTargetPageId="130" captionText="FIGURE 86. Range map of Berardius bairdii in Korea." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4571922" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4571922/files/figure.png" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">Fig. 86</figureCitation>
). Several strandings and by-catch in the East Sea are recorded every year (
<bibRefCitation author="Kim" box="[1175,1294,188,213]" firstAuthor="Kim" pageId="130" pageNumber="131" pagination="184 - 254" refId="ref107731" refString="Kim, Z. G. (2004) Suborder Pinnipedia &amp; Order Cetacea. In: Won, B. O. (Ed.), The mammals of Korea. Dongbang Media Press, Seoul, pp. 184 - 254. [in Korean]" type="book chapter" year="2004">Kim 2004</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
